<div class="container py-5">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-8">
      <h1 class="mb-4">Family Planning & Contraception</h1>
      <p class="lead mb-4">Evidence-based information about contraception options, fertility awareness, and planning for pregnancy on your own terms.</p>
      
      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Understanding Contraception Options</h5>
          
          <p>Contraception methods vary in effectiveness, duration, hormonal content, and convenience. Finding the right method depends on your health, lifestyle, and family planning goals.</p>
          
          <div class="table-responsive">
            <table class="table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Method</th>
                  <th>Effectiveness</th>
                  <th>Duration</th>
                  <th>Hormonal</th>
                  <th>STI Protection</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>IUD (hormonal)</td>
                  <td>99%+</td>
                  <td>3-7 years</td>
                  <td>Yes (localized)</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>IUD (copper)</td>
                  <td>99%+</td>
                  <td>10-12 years</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Implant</td>
                  <td>99%+</td>
                  <td>3-5 years</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Birth Control Shot</td>
                  <td>94-99%</td>
                  <td>3 months</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Birth Control Pills</td>
                  <td>91-99%</td>
                  <td>Daily</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Patch</td>
                  <td>91-99%</td>
                  <td>Weekly</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Vaginal Ring</td>
                  <td>91-99%</td>
                  <td>Monthly</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Male Condom</td>
                  <td>85-98%</td>
                  <td>Single use</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Female Condom</td>
                  <td>79-95%</td>
                  <td>Single use</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                  <td>Yes</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Diaphragm with Spermicide</td>
                  <td>88-94%</td>
                  <td>Reusable</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Fertility Awareness</td>
                  <td>76-88%</td>
                  <td>Daily tracking</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Withdrawal</td>
                  <td>78-96%</td>
                  <td>Each time</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Sterilization</td>
                  <td>99%+</td>
                  <td>Permanent</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                  <td>No</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          
          <p class="mt-3"><small class="text-muted">Note: Effectiveness rates show typical use vs. perfect use. Actual effectiveness varies based on consistent and correct use.</small></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Hormonal Contraception Methods</h5>
          
          <div class="accordion" id="hormonalAccordion">
            <!-- Pills -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingPills">
                <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapsePills" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapsePills">
                  Birth Control Pills
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapsePills" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingPills" data-bs-parent="#hormonalAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                      <h6>Types:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li><strong>Combination pills:</strong> Contain estrogen and progestin</li>
                        <li><strong>Progestin-only pills (mini-pills):</strong> Contain only progestin</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>How they work:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Prevent ovulation</li>
                        <li>Thicken cervical mucus to block sperm</li>
                        <li>Thin uterine lining</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Benefits beyond contraception:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>More regular, lighter periods</li>
                        <li>Reduced menstrual cramps</li>
                        <li>Reduced risk of ovarian and endometrial cancers</li>
                        <li>May improve acne</li>
                        <li>Treatment for conditions like PCOS and endometriosis</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Considerations:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Must be taken consistently, ideally at the same time each day</li>
                        <li>No protection against STIs</li>
                        <li>May have side effects: spotting, breast tenderness, nausea, headaches</li>
                        <li>Some medical conditions or medications may interfere with effectiveness</li>
                        <li>Some risk factors may make hormonal methods less appropriate</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                      <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <h6>Effectiveness:</h6>
                        <p>With perfect use: 99%<br>With typical use: 91%</p>
                        <h6>Best for those who:</h6>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Can remember to take a pill daily</li>
                          <li>Want a method they can stop easily</li>
                          <li>Want menstrual benefits</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Patch -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingPatch">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapsePatch" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapsePatch">
                  Birth Control Patch
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapsePatch" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingPatch" data-bs-parent="#hormonalAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                      <h6>How it works:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Adhesive patch worn on the skin (abdomen, buttock, back, or upper arm)</li>
                        <li>Releases estrogen and progestin through the skin</li>
                        <li>Changed weekly for three weeks, with one patch-free week</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Benefits:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Only needs changing once a week</li>
                        <li>Not affected by vomiting or diarrhea</li>
                        <li>Similar benefits to birth control pills (regular periods, reduced cramps)</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Considerations:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>May be less effective in women weighing over 198 pounds</li>
                        <li>Can cause skin irritation at application site</li>
                        <li>Visible on skin</li>
                        <li>Similar side effects to pills</li>
                        <li>Slightly higher estrogen exposure than pills</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                      <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <h6>Effectiveness:</h6>
                        <p>With perfect use: 99%<br>With typical use: 91%</p>
                        <h6>Best for those who:</h6>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Might forget daily pills</li>
                          <li>Want a method they control</li>
                          <li>Don't mind a visible method</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Vaginal Ring -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingVaginalRing">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseVaginalRing" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseVaginalRing">
                  Vaginal Ring
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseVaginalRing" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingVaginalRing" data-bs-parent="#hormonalAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                      <h6>How it works:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Flexible ring inserted into the vagina</li>
                        <li>Releases estrogen and progestin</li>
                        <li>Left in place for three weeks, then removed for one week</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Benefits:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Monthly use - only need to remember twice a month</li>
                        <li>Not visible when in use</li>
                        <li>Does not interfere with sex (can be removed for up to 3 hours if desired)</li>
                        <li>Lower estrogen dose than most pills</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Considerations:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Requires comfort with inserting and removing from vagina</li>
                        <li>May cause increased vaginal discharge</li>
                        <li>Can occasionally be felt during intercourse</li>
                        <li>Similar side effects to other hormonal methods</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                      <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <h6>Effectiveness:</h6>
                        <p>With perfect use: 99%<br>With typical use: 91%</p>
                        <h6>Best for those who:</h6>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Want a low-maintenance method</li>
                          <li>Are comfortable with their bodies</li>
                          <li>Want a discreet option</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Injection -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingInjection">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseInjection" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseInjection">
                  Birth Control Shot
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseInjection" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingInjection" data-bs-parent="#hormonalAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                      <h6>How it works:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Injection of progestin (Depo-Provera)</li>
                        <li>Given every 12 weeks (3 months)</li>
                        <li>Prevents pregnancy primarily by stopping ovulation</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Benefits:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Only requires attention 4 times a year</li>
                        <li>Very private - no visible evidence</li>
                        <li>Can reduce or eliminate periods over time</li>
                        <li>Not affected by other medications</li>
                        <li>Safe for breastfeeding mothers</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Considerations:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Cannot be removed from the body once injected</li>
                        <li>May cause irregular bleeding, especially initially</li>
                        <li>Return to fertility may be delayed after stopping (average 10 months)</li>
                        <li>Potential for weight gain</li>
                        <li>May affect bone density with long-term use</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                      <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <h6>Effectiveness:</h6>
                        <p>With perfect use: 99%<br>With typical use: 94%</p>
                        <h6>Best for those who:</h6>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Want an effective, private method</li>
                          <li>Can make regular appointments</li>
                          <li>Don't mind injections</li>
                          <li>Aren't planning pregnancy soon</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Long-Acting Reversible Contraception (LARC)</h5>
          
          <p>LARCs are the most effective reversible contraceptive methods, with effectiveness rates over 99%.</p>
          
          <div class="accordion" id="larcAccordion">
            <!-- IUDs -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingIUD">
                <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseIUD" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseIUD">
                  Intrauterine Devices (IUDs)
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseIUD" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingIUD" data-bs-parent="#larcAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                      <h6>Types:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li><strong>Hormonal IUDs:</strong> Release progestin locally in the uterus (last 3-7 years depending on brand)</li>
                        <li><strong>Copper IUD:</strong> Non-hormonal, made of plastic wrapped with copper wire (lasts 10-12 years)</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>How they work:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Create an environment in the uterus that's inhospitable to sperm</li>
                        <li>Hormonal IUDs also thicken cervical mucus and may suppress ovulation</li>
                        <li>Copper IUDs create a spermicidal environment</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Benefits:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>"Set it and forget it" - no daily, weekly, or monthly action required</li>
                        <li>Hormonal IUDs often reduce menstrual bleeding and cramps</li>
                        <li>Copper IUD is completely non-hormonal</li>
                        <li>Quick return to fertility upon removal</li>
                        <li>Cost-effective over time</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Considerations:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Requires a healthcare provider for insertion and removal</li>
                        <li>May cause cramping during and shortly after insertion</li>
                        <li>Copper IUDs may cause heavier periods and cramping</li>
                        <li>Rare risk of expulsion, perforation, or infection</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                      <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <h6>Effectiveness:</h6>
                        <p>Over 99%</p>
                        <h6>Best for those who:</h6>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Want long-term, highly effective contraception</li>
                          <li>Prefer to avoid daily/weekly/monthly maintenance</li>
                          <li>Want reversible contraception</li>
                          <li>May or may not want reduced periods (depending on type)</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Implant -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingImplant">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseImplant" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseImplant">
                  Contraceptive Implant
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseImplant" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingImplant" data-bs-parent="#larcAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                      <h6>How it works:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Small, flexible rod inserted under the skin of the upper arm</li>
                        <li>Releases progestin continuously</li>
                        <li>Lasts for 3-5 years (depending on brand)</li>
                        <li>Primarily works by preventing ovulation</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Benefits:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Most effective form of reversible contraception</li>
                        <li>No need to remember daily, weekly, or monthly contraception</li>
                        <li>Discreet (typically not visible, may be felt under skin)</li>
                        <li>Quick return to fertility after removal</li>
                        <li>Can be used while breastfeeding</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Considerations:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Requires a minor procedure for insertion and removal</li>
                        <li>May cause irregular bleeding patterns, especially in the first 6-12 months</li>
                        <li>Some women experience regular periods, some have infrequent periods, and others have no periods</li>
                        <li>Other possible side effects include headaches, breast tenderness, and acne</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                      <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <h6>Effectiveness:</h6>
                        <p>Over 99%</p>
                        <h6>Best for those who:</h6>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Want the most effective reversible contraception</li>
                          <li>Prefer a method they don't have to think about</li>
                          <li>Are comfortable with potential changes in bleeding patterns</li>
                          <li>Want a discreet option</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Barrier Methods & Non-Hormonal Options</h5>
          
          <div class="accordion" id="barrierAccordion">
            <!-- Condoms -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingCondoms">
                <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseCondoms" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseCondoms">
                  Condoms (Male & Female)
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseCondoms" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingCondoms" data-bs-parent="#barrierAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                      <h6>Types:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li><strong>Male condoms:</strong> Thin sheaths that cover the penis</li>
                        <li><strong>Female condoms:</strong> Pouches inserted into the vagina</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>How they work:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Create a physical barrier that prevents sperm from entering the vagina/cervix</li>
                        <li>Most are made of latex, but non-latex options exist (polyurethane, polyisoprene)</li>
                        <li>Must be used correctly every time</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Benefits:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Only contraceptive method that protects against most STIs</li>
                        <li>Available without prescription</li>
                        <li>No hormonal side effects</li>
                        <li>Can be used as backup with other methods</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Considerations:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Must be used correctly every time to be effective</li>
                        <li>Must be put on/inserted before any genital contact</li>
                        <li>Some people may have latex allergies (alternatives available)</li>
                        <li>May reduce sensation for some people</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                      <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <h6>Effectiveness:</h6>
                        <p>Male condom:<br>Perfect use: 98%<br>Typical use: 85%</p>
                        <p>Female condom:<br>Perfect use: 95%<br>Typical use: 79%</p>
                        <h6>Best for those who:</h6>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Want STI protection</li>
                          <li>Prefer non-hormonal methods</li>
                          <li>Need an occasional or backup method</li>
                          <li>Want a method available immediately</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Diaphragm & Cervical Cap -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingDiaphragm">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseDiaphragm" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseDiaphragm">
                  Diaphragm & Cervical Cap
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseDiaphragm" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingDiaphragm" data-bs-parent="#barrierAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                      <h6>How they work:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Shallow cups made of silicone that cover the cervix</li>
                        <li>Must be used with spermicide</li>
                        <li>Inserted before sex and left in place for several hours after</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Benefits:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Can be inserted hours before intercourse</li>
                        <li>Reusable for 1-2 years with proper care</li>
                        <li>No hormonal side effects</li>
                        <li>Can be used while breastfeeding</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Considerations:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Requires fitting by a healthcare provider</li>
                        <li>Must be comfortable with insertion and removal</li>
                        <li>Needs to remain in place for 6 hours after intercourse</li>
                        <li>Less effective than hormonal methods or IUDs</li>
                        <li>No protection against STIs</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                      <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <h6>Effectiveness:</h6>
                        <p>Perfect use: 94%<br>Typical use: 88%</p>
                        <h6>Best for those who:</h6>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Want a non-hormonal option</li>
                          <li>Are comfortable with their bodies</li>
                          <li>Can plan ahead for sexual activity</li>
                          <li>Are in monogamous relationships</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Fertility Awareness -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFAM">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFAM" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFAM">
                  Fertility Awareness Methods
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseFAM" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFAM" data-bs-parent="#barrierAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                      <h6>How they work:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Track fertility signs to identify fertile days</li>
                        <li>Avoid intercourse or use barriers during fertile periods</li>
                        <li>Methods include calendar tracking, cervical mucus monitoring, basal body temperature, and symptothermal methods</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Benefits:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>No devices or hormones</li>
                        <li>No cost after initial education</li>
                        <li>Aligns with certain religious beliefs</li>
                        <li>Increases body awareness</li>
                        <li>Can be used to prevent or achieve pregnancy</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Considerations:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Requires consistent daily tracking and record keeping</li>
                        <li>Needs significant education and practice</li>
                        <li>Less effective than most other methods</li>
                        <li>Requires periods of abstinence or backup methods</li>
                        <li>May be difficult with irregular cycles</li>
                        <li>No STI protection</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                      <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <h6>Effectiveness:</h6>
                        <p>Perfect use: 88-98% (depending on specific method)<br>Typical use: 76-88%</p>
                        <h6>Best for those who:</h6>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Want a completely natural approach</li>
                          <li>Have religious or personal objections to other methods</li>
                          <li>Can maintain consistent daily tracking</li>
                          <li>Have regular cycles</li>
                          <li>Have partner support</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Permanent -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingPermanent">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapsePermanent" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapsePermanent">
                  Permanent Contraception
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapsePermanent" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingPermanent" data-bs-parent="#barrierAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                      <h6>Types:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li><strong>Female sterilization (tubal ligation):</strong> Cutting, tying, or blocking the fallopian tubes</li>
                        <li><strong>Male sterilization (vasectomy):</strong> Cutting or blocking the vas deferens</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>How they work:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Permanently prevents eggs and sperm from meeting</li>
                        <li>Tubal ligation requires surgery; vasectomy is an office procedure</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Benefits:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>One-time procedure for permanent contraception</li>
                        <li>No need to think about birth control again</li>
                        <li>No hormonal side effects</li>
                        <li>Highly effective</li>
                      </ul>
                      <h6>Considerations:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Should be considered permanent (reversal is expensive, complex, and not always successful)</li>
                        <li>Surgical risks (though minimal)</li>
                        <li>No protection against STIs</li>
                        <li>Requires absolute certainty about not wanting future pregnancies</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4">
                      <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <h6>Effectiveness:</h6>
                        <p>Over 99%</p>
                        <h6>Best for those who:</h6>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Are certain they don't want future pregnancies</li>
                          <li>Want a one-time solution</li>
                          <li>May have medical reasons to avoid pregnancy</li>
                          <li>Have completed their family size</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Emergency Contraception</h5>
          
          <p>Emergency contraception can prevent pregnancy after unprotected sex or contraceptive failure. It's not intended as a regular method of birth control.</p>
          
          <div class="table-responsive">
            <table class="table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Type</th>
                  <th>How it Works</th>
                  <th>Timeframe</th>
                  <th>Effectiveness</th>
                  <th>Access</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>Levonorgestrel Pills<br>(Plan B One-Step, Next Choice)</td>
                  <td>Delays ovulation; prevents fertilization</td>
                  <td>Most effective within 72 hours (3 days); can be used up to 5 days</td>
                  <td>75-89%</td>
                  <td>Available over-the-counter</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Ulipristal Acetate<br>(Ella)</td>
                  <td>Delays ovulation; more effective than progestin pills</td>
                  <td>Effective up to 5 days (120 hours)</td>
                  <td>85-95%</td>
                  <td>Prescription required</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Copper IUD</td>
                  <td>Prevents fertilization; may prevent implantation</td>
                  <td>Most effective when inserted within 5 days</td>
                  <td>99%+</td>
                  <td>Requires healthcare provider insertion</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          
          <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3">
            <p><strong>Important notes:</strong></p>
            <ul class="mb-0">
              <li>Emergency contraception is not effective if you're already pregnant</li>
              <li>It doesn't protect against STIs</li>
              <li>Higher body weight may reduce effectiveness of pill methods</li>
              <li>Regular contraception should be continued or started after using emergency contraception</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
